    "Hired initially by the wealthy New York art collecting elite to validate their tastes by creating a museum for their art, he acted as their advisor and procurer of art during the early years when the Museum bought almost no art at all.": [],
    "Much has been written about the \"eye\" of Barr, (i.e., his ability to identify the highest quality work of art).": [],
    "The works he selected for the museum and its benefactors (many of which were eventually donated to the the Museum) formed the canon of modern art history.": [
